          "TITLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "-MEASUREMENT OF TH-232(N,2N)TH-231 REACTION CROSS SEC-",
                " TION WITH 14 MEV NEUTRONS."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "CCW"
                ],
                "institute": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " NEUTRON GENERATOR AT THE KYOTO UNIVERSITY CRI-",
                " TICAL ASSEMBLIES, KUCA."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "D-T"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " THE NEUTRONS WERE PRODUCED BY BOMBARDING A TI-T",
                " TARGET WITH A 212 KEV BEAM OF 20 MICROAMPS AVERAGE",
                " BEAM CURRENT."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".THE AVERAGE NEUTRON ENERGY WAS DETERMINED BY THE REAC-",
                " TION RATIO OF ZR-90(N,2N) AND NB-93(N,2N), USING FOUR",
                " ZR AND FIVE NB FOILS AT A DISTANCE OF 4.4 CM FROM THE",
                " TI-T TARGET. FROM THE OBTAINED REACTION RATIO 1.67+/-",
                " 0.04, THE AVERAGE NEUTRON ENERGY WAS DETERMINED TO",
                " 14.7+/-0.1 MEV. THE FLUX DISTRIBUTION AND ENERGY",
                " SPECTRUM OF THE NEUTRONS IN THE THORIUM SAMPLES WERE",
                " CALCULATED WITH THE MONTE CARLO CODE MCNP, USING THE",
                " OKTAVIAN SOURCE NEUTRON SPECTRUM."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".THREE POLYETHYLENE PACKS OF THORIUM NITRATE POWDER OF",
                " ABOUT 500 MG WEIGHT WERE USED. THE THORIUM SAMPLES",
                " WERE SANDWICHED WITH 0.5 MM THICK ALUMINUM FOILS FOR",
                " NEUTRON FLUENCE MONITORING. THE DISTANCE BETWEEN THE",
                " TI-T TARGET AND THE FRONT SURFACE OF THE SAMPLES WAS",
                " 1.6 CM. THE SAMPLES WERE IRRADIATED FOR ABOUT 7.5 HRS.",
                " AFTER IRRADIATION THE SAMPLES WERE CHEMICALLY PURI-",
                " FIED."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " THE ACTIVITIES WERE MEASURED WITH A CALIBRATED",
                " PURE GERMANIUM DETECTOR. THE ABSOLUTE TH-231 ACTIVITY",
                " WAS DETERMINED BY COMPARISON WITH THE ACTIVITY FROM",
                " A 90 PERCENT ENRICHED URANIUM-ALUMINUM ALLOY WHICH",
                " CONTAINS TH-231.",
                ".THE TIME DEPENDENCE OF THE NEUTRON FLUX WAS MONITORED",
                " USING A MODERATOR TYPE NEUTRON DOSE RATE METER LOCATED",
                " ABOUT 2 M FROM THE TI-T TARGET."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "PART-DET": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
